\begin_layout Subsection*
a.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Consider starting at a steady state and introducing a marginal cost shock
 (
\begin_inset Formula $u_{t}>0$
\end_inset

).
 Intuitively, the 
\series bold
supply
\series default
 curve will shift 
\series bold
upwards
\series default
, because of an increase in price.
 The effect on the variables on the model will be: increase in inflation,
 increase in interest rate (as the CB tries to stabilize the economy, slow
 down the shock and prevent a sudden shift).
 The 
\series bold
demand
\series default
 curve shifts to the 
\series bold
left
\series default
 and, and the output decreases.
\end_layout

